{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Mh8dHV7teB3KbPhLV6E1Zw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Comprehensive Project Overview:\n\n1. Project Structure\nThis is a Cargo Tracking application built using Quarkus, a Kubernetes Native Java stack. The project follows a domain-driven design (DDD) architecture with multiple layers:\n\n- Domain Layer: Contains core business logic and domain models\n  - `org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model`\n  - Packages: cargo, handling, location, voyage\n  - Includes value objects, entities, and repositories\n\n- Application Layer: Contains application services and business workflows\n  - `org.eclipse.cargotracker.application`\n  - Services: BookingService, HandlingEventService, CargoInspectionService\n\n- Infrastructure Layer: Implements technical capabilities\n  - `org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure`\n  - Subpackages for persistence (JPA), messaging (JMS), routing\n\n- Interfaces Layer: Web and external interfaces\n  - `org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces`\n  - Web controllers, DTOs, facades\n\n2. Technology Stack\n- Framework: Quarkus\n- Database: H2 (embedded)\n- ORM: Hibernate with Panache\n- Messaging: Qpid JMS\n- Validation: Hibernate Validator\n- Testing: JUnit 5, Rest Assured\n- UI: Primefaces with JSF\n- Build Tool: Maven\n\n3. Key Features\n- Cargo booking and tracking\n- Handling event registration\n- Route planning\n- Realtime cargo tracking\n- Batch processing for handling events\n- RESTful web services\n\n4. Notable Configuration\n- Uses Quarkus native image compilation\n- Configurable JMS queues\n- Supports test and production profiles\n- Database schema management\n- Extensive logging configuration\n\n5. Notable Patterns\n- Repository pattern for data access\n- Specification pattern for business rules\n- DTO assemblers for mapping\n- Event-driven architecture\n- Dependency Injection (CDI)\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the project structure or architecture?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"26f97540-be94-4ce2-a5d3-203776c82a58"}
