{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VseJBkdVp4xw2rE1Mkrf6N","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    11→\n    12→public interface HandlingEventService {\n    13→\n    14→  /**\n    15→   * Registers a handling event in the system, and notifies interested parties that a cargo has been\n    16→   * handled.\n    17→   */\n    18→  void registerHandlingEvent(\n    19→      @NotNull(message = \"Completion time is required.\") LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    20→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    21→      @Valid VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    22→      @NotNull(message = \"Location is required.\") @Valid UnLocode unLocode,\n    23→      @NotNull(message = \"Type is required.\") HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    24→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"30a0726f-73be-4347-8998-bedc2f8704fe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VWqznR6X4TJxvdkgXNmzEp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     6→\n     7→public interface CargoInspectionService {\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * Inspect cargo and send relevant notifications to interested parties, for example if a cargo has\n    11→   * been misdirected, or unloaded at the final destination.\n    12→   */\n    13→  public void inspectCargo(\n    14→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"963b2c1c-3cd4-49fb-9622-50c10c4dcc67"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NNKXXf4uJ9Z7dsvJHhr3AR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * This interface provides a way to let other parts of the system know about events that have\n     9→ * occurred.\n    10→ *\n    11→ * <p>It may be implemented synchronously or asynchronously, using for example JMS.\n    12→ */\n    13→public interface ApplicationEvents {\n    14→\n    15→  void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event);\n    16→\n    17→  void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo);\n    18→\n    19→  void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo);\n    20→\n    21→  void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt);\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"62bc90e7-9d42-4021-894d-bbf45449a950"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011tyzbruwaTzzM7oAKd2e6V","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Future;\n     7→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    11→\n    12→/** Cargo booking service. */\n    13→public interface BookingService {\n    14→\n    15→    /** Registers a new cargo in the tracking system, not yet routed. */\n    16→    TrackingId bookNewCargo(\n    17→            @NotNull(message = \"Origin is required.\") @Valid UnLocode origin,\n    18→            @NotNull(message = \"Destination is required.\") @Valid UnLocode destination,\n    19→            @NotNull(message = \"Deadline is required.\") @Future(\n    20→                    message = \"Deadline must be in the future.\") LocalDate arrivalDeadline);\n    21→\n    22→    /**\n    23→     * Requests a list of itineraries describing possible routes for this cargo.\n    24→     *\n    25→     * @param trackingId Cargo tracking ID\n    26→     * @return A list of possible itineraries for this cargo\n    27→     */\n    28→    List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(\n    29→            @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    30→\n    31→    void assignCargoToRoute(\n    32→            @NotNull(message = \"Itinerary is required.\") @Valid Itinerary itinerary,\n    33→            @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    34→\n    35→    void changeDestination(\n    36→            @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    37→            @NotNull(message = \"Destination is required.\") @Valid UnLocode unLocode);\n    38→\n    39→    void changeDeadline(\n    40→            @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    41→            @NotNull(message = \"Deadline is required.\") @Future(\n    42→                    message = \"Deadline must be in the future.\") LocalDate deadline);\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"c95313fe-22c7-4f4a-9437-88c07d6435f6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CzAwoscobLpd6CAtSCXjZU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import io.quarkus.arc.profile.UnlessBuildProfile;\n     7→import io.quarkus.runtime.Startup;\n     8→\n     9→/** Loads sample data for demo. */\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→@Startup\n    12→@UnlessBuildProfile(\"test\") // disable for tests\n    13→public class SampleDataGenerator {\n    14→\n    15→  @Inject\n    16→  private InitLoader loader;\n    17→\n    18→  @PostConstruct\n    19→  public void loadSampleData() {\n    20→    loader.loadData();\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"04d6c6ae-816c-45ea-ba26-6100a7f757b6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018eMfJW1Rdaa9n5UNvQ9fQY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.ZoneId;\n     6→import java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter;\n     7→\n     8→// TODO [Clean Code] Make this a CDI singleton?\n     9→public class DateConverter {\n    10→  public static final String DATE_FORMAT = \"M/d/yyyy\";\n    11→  public static final String DATE_TIME_FORMAT = \"M/d/yyyy h:m a\";\n    12→\n    13→  private static final DateTimeFormatter DATE_FORMATTER =\n    14→      DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(DATE_FORMAT).withZone(ZoneId.systemDefault());\n    15→\n    16→  private static final DateTimeFormatter DATE_TIME_FORMATTER =\n    17→      DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(DATE_TIME_FORMAT).withZone(ZoneId.systemDefault());\n    18→\n    19→  private DateConverter() {}\n    20→\n    21→  public static LocalDate toDate(String date) {\n    22→    return LocalDate.parse(date, DATE_FORMATTER);\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  public static LocalDateTime toDateTime(String datetime) {\n    26→    return LocalDateTime.parse(datetime, DATE_TIME_FORMATTER);\n    27→  }\n    28→\n    29→  public static String toString(LocalDateTime dateTime) {\n    30→    return dateTime.format(DATE_TIME_FORMATTER);\n    31→  }\n    32→\n    33→  public static String toString(LocalDate date) {\n    34→    return date.format(DATE_FORMATTER);\n    35→  }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"9a4d77c0-7939-4d48-acb8-6d6a8da28a4e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014cv1T2ihgJTT6QzDwxWcTn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→/** Jakarta REST configuration. */\n     7→@ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\n     8→public class RestConfiguration extends Application {\n     9→}\n    10→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"2ce7a4e0-3160-460d-a480-12aeffd24875"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lex1dAFBsdbJfamoRH5bSZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * Application settings. Although this is stored in the database, it is not a true part of the\n     9→ * domain model but simply an application infrastructure artifact.\n    10→ */\n    11→@Entity\n    12→public class ApplicationSettings implements Serializable {\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  @Id\n    16→  private Long id;\n    17→\n    18→  private boolean sampleLoaded = false;\n    19→\n    20→  public boolean isSampleLoaded() {\n    21→    return sampleLoaded;\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public void setSampleLoaded(boolean sampleLoaded) {\n    25→    this.sampleLoaded = sampleLoaded;\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"c0de3029-58c2-488f-a66d-b3d760e5f71c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Cn9veXn4VvrEraiipjZdHa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.Arrays;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventFactory;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.SampleVoyages;\n    19→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    20→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    21→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    22→import jakarta.persistence.LockModeType;\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.NoResultException;\n    24→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    25→\n    26→@ApplicationScoped\n    27→public class InitLoader {\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject\n    30→  private Logger logger;\n    31→\n    32→  @Inject\n    33→  private EntityManager entityManager;\n    34→  @Inject\n    35→  private HandlingEventFactory handlingEventFactory;\n    36→  @Inject\n    37→  private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    38→\n    39→  @Transactional\n    40→  public void loadData() {\n    41→    if (!isSampleLoaded()) {\n    42→      logger.info(\"Loading sample data.\");\n    43→      loadSampleLocations();\n    44→      loadSampleVoyages();\n    45→      loadSampleCargos();\n    46→    } else {\n    47→      logger.info(\"Sample data already loaded, skipping.\");\n    48→    }\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  private boolean isSampleLoaded() {\n    52→    boolean sampleLoaded = false;\n    53→\n    54→    try {\n    55→      ApplicationSettings settings =\n    56→          entityManager.find(ApplicationSettings.class, 1L, LockModeType.PESSIMISTIC_WRITE);\n    57→      sampleLoaded = settings.isSampleLoaded();\n    58→      settings.setSampleLoaded(true);\n    59→    } catch (NoResultException e) {\n    60→      throw new RuntimeException(\"Could not retrieve application settings.\", e);\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    return sampleLoaded;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  private void loadSampleLocations() {\n    67→    logger.info(\"Loading sample locations.\");\n    68→\n    69→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HONGKONG);\n    70→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.MELBOURNE);\n    71→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM);\n    72→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HELSINKI);\n    73→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.CHICAGO);\n    74→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.TOKYO);\n    75→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HAMBURG);\n    76→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.SHANGHAI);\n    77→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM);\n    78→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG);\n    79→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HANGZOU);\n    80→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.NEWYORK);\n    81→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.DALLAS);\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  private void loadSampleVoyages() {\n    85→    logger.info(\"Loading sample voyages.\");\n    86→\n    87→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK);\n    88→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS);\n    89→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI);\n    90→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.HELSINKI_TO_HONGKONG);\n    91→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI_ALT);\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  private void loadSampleCargos() {\n    95→    logger.info(\"Loading sample cargo data.\");\n    96→\n    97→    // Cargo ABC123. This one is en-route.\n    98→    TrackingId trackingId1 = new TrackingId(\"ABC123\");\n    99→\n   100→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification1 =\n   101→        new RouteSpecification(\n   102→            SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.HELSINKI, LocalDate.now().plusDays(15));\n   103→    Cargo abc123 = new Cargo(trackingId1, routeSpecification1);\n   104→\n   105→    Itinerary itinerary1 =\n   106→        new Itinerary(\n   107→            Arrays.asList(\n   108→                new Leg(\n   109→                    SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK,\n   110→                    SampleLocations.HONGKONG,\n   111→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   112→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(7).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(4),\n   113→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(1).minusHours(10).minusMinutes(52)),\n   114→                new Leg(\n   115→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   116→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   117→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   118→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(2).minusHours(18).minusMinutes(38),\n   119→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(6).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(22)),\n   120→                new Leg(\n   121→                    SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI,\n   122→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   123→                    SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n   124→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(8).minusHours(8).minusMinutes(18),\n   125→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(14).minusHours(12).minusMinutes(29))));\n   126→    abc123.assignToRoute(itinerary1);\n   127→\n   128→    entityManager.persist(abc123);\n   129→\n   130→    try {\n   131→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   132→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   133→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(5).minusMinutes(5),\n   134→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(9).minusMinutes(11),\n   135→              trackingId1,\n   136→              null,\n   137→              SampleLocations.HONGKONG.getUnLocode(),\n   138→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   139→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   140→\n   141→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   142→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   143→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(6).minusMinutes(46),\n   144→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(7).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(50),\n   145→              trackingId1,\n   146→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   147→              SampleLocations.HONGKONG.getUnLocode(),\n   148→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   149→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   150→\n   151→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   152→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   153→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(15).minusMinutes(26),\n   154→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(1).minusHours(4).minusMinutes(32),\n   155→              trackingId1,\n   156→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   157→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   158→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   159→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   160→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   161→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   162→    }\n   163→\n   164→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory1 =\n   165→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId1);\n   166→    abc123.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory1);\n   167→\n   168→    entityManager.persist(abc123);\n   169→\n   170→    // Cargo JKL567. This one was loaded on the wrong voyage.\n   171→    TrackingId trackingId2 = new TrackingId(\"JKL567\");\n   172→\n   173→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification2 =\n   174→        new RouteSpecification(\n   175→            SampleLocations.HANGZOU, SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM, LocalDate.now().plusDays(18));\n   176→    Cargo jkl567 = new Cargo(trackingId2, routeSpecification2);\n   177→\n   178→    Itinerary itinerary2 =\n   179→        new Itinerary(\n   180→            Arrays.asList(\n   181→                new Leg(\n   182→                    SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK,\n   183→                    SampleLocations.HANGZOU,\n   184→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   185→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(1).minusMinutes(19),\n   186→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(3).minusHours(7).minusMinutes(2)),\n   187→                new Leg(\n   188→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   189→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   190→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   191→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(2).minusHours(17).minusMinutes(3),\n   192→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(2).minusHours(5).minusMinutes(20)),\n   193→                new Leg(\n   194→                    SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI,\n   195→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   196→                    SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n   197→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(6).minusHours(11).minusMinutes(38),\n   198→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(15).minusHours(4).minusMinutes(1))));\n   199→    jkl567.assignToRoute(itinerary2);\n   200→\n   201→    entityManager.persist(jkl567);\n   202→\n   203→    try {\n   204→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   205→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   206→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(2).minusMinutes(44),\n   207→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(15).minusHours(14).minusMinutes(33),\n   208→              trackingId2,\n   209→              null,\n   210→              SampleLocations.HANGZOU.getUnLocode(),\n   211→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   212→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   213→\n   214→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   215→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   216→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(12),\n   217→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(17),\n   218→              trackingId2,\n   219→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   220→              SampleLocations.HANGZOU.getUnLocode(),\n   221→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   222→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   223→\n   224→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   225→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   226→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(21),\n   227→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(3).minusHours(22).minusMinutes(1),\n   228→              trackingId2,\n   229→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   230→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   231→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   232→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   233→\n   234→      // The wrong voyage!\n   235→      HandlingEvent event4 =\n   236→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   237→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(18).minusMinutes(36),\n   238→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(2).minusHours(8).minusMinutes(7),\n   239→              trackingId2,\n   240→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   241→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   242→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   243→      entityManager.persist(event4);\n   244→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   245→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   246→    }\n   247→\n   248→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory2 =\n   249→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId2);\n   250→    jkl567.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory2);\n   251→\n   252→    entityManager.persist(jkl567);\n   253→\n   254→    // Cargo definition DEF789. This one will remain un-routed.\n   255→    TrackingId trackingId3 = new TrackingId(\"DEF789\");\n   256→\n   257→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification3 =\n   258→        new RouteSpecification(\n   259→            SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.MELBOURNE, LocalDate.now().plusMonths(2));\n   260→\n   261→    Cargo def789 = new Cargo(trackingId3, routeSpecification3);\n   262→    entityManager.persist(def789);\n   263→\n   264→    // Cargo definition MNO456. This one will be claimed properly.\n   265→    TrackingId trackingId4 = new TrackingId(\"MNO456\");\n   266→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification4 =\n   267→        new RouteSpecification(\n   268→            SampleLocations.NEWYORK, SampleLocations.DALLAS, LocalDate.now().minusDays(24));\n   269→\n   270→    Cargo mno456 = new Cargo(trackingId4, routeSpecification4);\n   271→\n   272→    Itinerary itinerary4 =\n   273→        new Itinerary(\n   274→            Arrays.asList(\n   275→                new Leg(\n   276→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   277→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   278→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   279→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(34).minusHours(1).minusMinutes(1),\n   280→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(28).minusHours(10).minusMinutes(1))));\n   281→\n   282→    mno456.assignToRoute(itinerary4);\n   283→    entityManager.persist(mno456);\n   284→\n   285→    try {\n   286→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   287→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   288→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(16).minusMinutes(9),\n   289→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(37).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(21),\n   290→              trackingId4,\n   291→              null,\n   292→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   293→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   294→\n   295→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   296→\n   297→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   298→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   299→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(9),\n   300→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(34).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(8),\n   301→              trackingId4,\n   302→              SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS.getVoyageNumber(),\n   303→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   304→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   305→\n   306→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   307→\n   308→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   309→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   310→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(14).minusMinutes(10),\n   311→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(28).minusHours(7).minusMinutes(7),\n   312→              trackingId4,\n   313→              SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS.getVoyageNumber(),\n   314→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   315→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   316→\n   317→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   318→\n   319→      HandlingEvent event4 =\n   320→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   321→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(22).minusMinutes(1),\n   322→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(27).minusHours(18).minusMinutes(3),\n   323→              trackingId4,\n   324→              null,\n   325→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   326→              HandlingEvent.Type.CUSTOMS);\n   327→\n   328→      entityManager.persist(event4);\n   329→\n   330→      HandlingEvent event5 =\n   331→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   332→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(9).minusMinutes(30),\n   333→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(26).minusHours(14).minusMinutes(15),\n   334→              trackingId4,\n   335→              null,\n   336→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   337→              HandlingEvent.Type.CLAIM);\n   338→\n   339→      entityManager.persist(event5);\n   340→\n   341→      HandlingHistory handlingHistory3 =\n   342→          handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId4);\n   343→\n   344→      mno456.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory3);\n   345→\n   346→      entityManager.persist(mno456);\n   347→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   348→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   349→    }\n   350→  }\n   351→\n   352→}\n   353→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"5192ddf2-efec-4730-a11b-d15edafa8060"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016Yb7DKmaVsVbi7hQU8LEWW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.HandlingEventService;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventFactory;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    15→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    16→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    17→\n    18→@ApplicationScoped\n    19→@Transactional(rollbackOn = CannotCreateHandlingEventException.class)\n    20→public class DefaultHandlingEventService implements HandlingEventService {\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject\n    23→  private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    24→  @Inject\n    25→  private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    26→  @Inject\n    27→  private HandlingEventFactory handlingEventFactory;\n    28→  @Inject\n    29→  private Logger logger;\n    30→\n    31→  @Override\n    32→  public void registerHandlingEvent(\n    33→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    34→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    35→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    36→      UnLocode unLocode,\n    37→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    38→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    39→    LocalDateTime registrationTime = LocalDateTime.now();\n    40→\n    41→    /*\n    42→     * Using a factory to create a HandlingEvent (aggregate). This is where it is determined wether\n    43→     * the incoming data, the attempt, actually is capable of representing a real handling event.\n    44→     */\n    45→    HandlingEvent event =\n    46→        handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n    47→            registrationTime, completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, unLocode, type);\n    48→\n    49→    /*\n    50→     * Store the new handling event, which updates the persistent state of the handling event\n    51→     * aggregate (but not the cargo aggregate - that happens asynchronously!)\n    52→     */\n    53→    handlingEventRepository.store(event);\n    54→\n    55→    /* Publish an event stating that a cargo has been handled. */\n    56→    applicationEvents.cargoWasHandled(event);\n    57→\n    58→    logger.info(\"Registered handling event\");\n    59→  }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"2abc9873-c991-4742-9f67-d993fdca05a7"}
