{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RbLx2m64rKewGDZZUnPAT6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n     7→\n     8→@XmlRootElement\n     9→public class TransitPaths implements Serializable {\n    10→\n    11→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    12→\n    13→    private List<TransitPath> transitPaths;\n    14→\n    15→    public TransitPaths() {\n    16→        this.transitPaths = new ArrayList<>();\n    17→    }\n    18→\n    19→    public TransitPaths(List<TransitPath> transitPaths) {\n    20→        this.transitPaths = transitPaths;\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→    public List<TransitPath> getTransitPaths() {\n    24→        return transitPaths;\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    public void setTransitPaths(List<TransitPath> transitPaths) {\n    28→        this.transitPaths = transitPaths;\n    29→    }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"48d59e98-befb-471a-9c0d-6457c78aa41a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q1K9EZuk6CNaVVnf75XXf6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.Arrays;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Random;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class GraphDao implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  private final Random random = new Random();\n    16→\n    17→  public List<String> listLocations() {\n    18→    return new ArrayList<>(\n    19→        Arrays.asList(\n    20→            \"CNHKG\", \"AUMEL\", \"SESTO\", \"FIHEL\", \"USCHI\", \"JNTKO\", \"DEHAM\", \"CNSHA\", \"NLRTM\",\n    21→            \"SEGOT\", \"CNHGH\", \"USNYC\", \"USDAL\"));\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public String getVoyageNumber(String from, String to) {\n    25→    int i = random.nextInt(5);\n    26→\n    27→    switch (i) {\n    28→      case 0:\n    29→        return \"0100S\";\n    30→      case 1:\n    31→        return \"0200T\";\n    32→      case 2:\n    33→        return \"0300A\";\n    34→      case 3:\n    35→        return \"0301S\";\n    36→      default:\n    37→        return \"0400S\";\n    38→    }\n    39→  }\n    40→}\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"3ae7ebfe-8c5e-432d-8adf-4fd02abaabc3"}
