{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y9fyBcCYrWzHpLuQseZ9o7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    12→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    16→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    17→ * the tracking user interface.\n    18→ *\n    19→ * <p>\n    20→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    21→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    22→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    23→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    24→ */\n    25→@Named\n    26→@ViewScoped\n    27→public class ChangeDestination implements Serializable {\n    28→\n    29→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    30→\n    31→  @Inject\n    32→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    33→\n    34→  private String trackingId;\n    35→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    36→  private List<Location> locations;\n    37→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    38→\n    39→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    40→    return trackingId;\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    44→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    48→    return cargo;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    52→    return locations;\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public List<Location> getPotentialDestinations() {\n    56→    // Potential destination = All Locations - Origin - Current Destination\n    57→    List<Location> destinationsToRemove =\n    58→        locations\n    59→            .stream()\n    60→            .filter(\n    61→                location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(cargo.getOriginCode())\n    62→                    || location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(cargo.getFinalDestinationCode()))\n    63→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    64→\n    65→    locations.removeAll(destinationsToRemove);\n    66→\n    67→    return locations;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n    71→    return destinationUnlocode;\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n    75→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n    76→  }\n    77→\n    78→  public void load() {\n    79→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    80→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  public void changeDestination() {\n    84→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnlocode);\n    85→    // PF.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    86→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    87→    // RequestContext.getCurrentInstance().closeDialog(\"DONE\");\n    88→  }\n    89→}\n    90→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"034d0954-50a4-4a78-9861-5938c0d1f8fa"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xwPp8hVXpaAH11ovi2Wky","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.HashMap;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Map;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    11→import org.primefaces.event.SelectEvent;\n    12→\n    13→@Named\n    14→@SessionScoped\n    15→public class ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog implements Serializable {\n    16→\n    17→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    18→\n    19→  public void showDialog(String trackingId) {\n    20→    Map<String, Object> options = new HashMap<>();\n    21→    options.put(\"modal\", true);\n    22→    options.put(\"draggable\", true);\n    23→    options.put(\"resizable\", false);\n    24→    options.put(\"contentWidth\", 410);\n    25→    options.put(\"contentHeight\", 280);\n    26→\n    27→    Map<String, List<String>> params = new HashMap<>();\n    28→    List<String> values = new ArrayList<>();\n    29→    values.add(trackingId);\n    30→    params.put(\"trackingId\", values);\n    31→\n    32→    PrimeFaces.current()\n    33→        .dialog()\n    34→        .openDynamic(\"/admin/dialogs/change_arrival_deadline.xhtml\", options, params);\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public void handleReturn(@SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\") SelectEvent event) {}\n    38→\n    39→  public void cancel() {\n    40→    // just kill the dialog\n    41→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"\");\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"60d6972b-6266-4288-9794-c7958c599a12"}
