{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QZf5u28QriZzkmnajT64UE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    15→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    16→ * the tracking user interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>\n    19→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    20→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    21→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    22→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    23→ */\n    24→@Named\n    25→@ViewScoped\n    26→public class ChangeArrivalDeadline implements Serializable {\n    27→\n    28→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    29→\n    30→  @Inject\n    31→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    32→\n    33→  private String trackingId;\n    34→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    35→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    36→\n    37→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    38→    return trackingId;\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    42→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    46→    return cargo;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n    50→    return arrivalDeadline;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    54→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public void load() {\n    58→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    59→    arrivalDeadline = DateConverter.toDate(cargo.getArrivalDeadline());\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public void changeArrivalDeadline() {\n    63→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDeadline(trackingId, arrivalDeadline);\n    64→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    65→  }\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"d918a22a-da91-4344-83d3-d29bc3b1dd46"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XgM7Q3bBiNYN1t9jRgX8bj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled;\n     4→import jakarta.batch.operations.JobOperator;\n     5→import jakarta.batch.runtime.BatchRuntime;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Periodically scans a certain directory for files and attempts to parse handling event\n    11→ * registrations from the contents by calling a batch job.\n    12→ *\n    13→ * <p>\n    14→ * Files that fail to parse are moved into a separate directory, successful files are deleted.\n    15→ */\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→@Transactional\n    18→public class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n    19→\n    20→  @Scheduled(every = \"2m\") // In production, run every fifteen minutes\n    21→  public void processFiles() {\n    22→    JobOperator jobOperator = BatchRuntime.getJobOperator();\n    23→    jobOperator.start(\"EventFilesProcessorJob\", null);\n    24→  }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"f20b75c4-fbc0-4ad9-af4b-08b7dda2e0d1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KgFBLM4w2Yvzt1ac1sgP5d","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→public class EventLineParseException extends RuntimeException {\n     4→\n     5→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n     6→\n     7→  private final String line;\n     8→\n     9→  public EventLineParseException(String message, Throwable cause, String line) {\n    10→    super(message, cause);\n    11→    this.line = line;\n    12→  }\n    13→\n    14→  public EventLineParseException(String message, String line) {\n    15→    super(message);\n    16→    this.line = line;\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  public String getLine() {\n    20→    return line;\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"fad4c52a-38d0-4d95-9fc5-5c30cbb25ad5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019ikSQcNHiB1Cbt5LBUXKRD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.BufferedWriter;\n     4→import java.io.File;\n     5→import java.io.FileWriter;\n     6→import java.io.PrintWriter;\n     7→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     8→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     9→import jakarta.batch.api.chunk.listener.SkipReadListener;\n    10→import jakarta.batch.runtime.context.JobContext;\n    11→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    14→\n    15→@Dependent\n    16→@Named(\"LineParseExceptionListener\")\n    17→public class LineParseExceptionListener implements SkipReadListener {\n    18→\n    19→  private static final String FAILED_DIRECTORY = \"failed_directory\";\n    20→\n    21→  @Inject\n    22→  private Logger logger;\n    23→\n    24→  @Inject\n    25→  private JobContext jobContext;\n    26→\n    27→  @Override\n    28→  public void onSkipReadItem(Exception e) throws Exception {\n    29→    File failedDirectory = new File(jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(FAILED_DIRECTORY));\n    30→\n    31→    if (!failedDirectory.exists()) {\n    32→      failedDirectory.mkdirs();\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→    EventLineParseException parseException = (EventLineParseException) e;\n    36→\n    37→    logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Problem parsing event file line\", parseException);\n    38→\n    39→    try (PrintWriter failed =\n    40→        new PrintWriter(\n    41→            new BufferedWriter(\n    42→                new FileWriter(\n    43→                    new File(\n    44→                        failedDirectory,\n    45→                        \"failed_\"\n    46→                            + jobContext.getJobName()\n    47→                            + \"_\"\n    48→                            + jobContext.getInstanceId()\n    49→                            + \".csv\"),\n    50→                    true)))) {\n    51→      failed.println(parseException.getLine());\n    52→    }\n    53→  }\n    54→}\n    55→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"0e4a044b-f8b2-4021-8393-f97d2fd17db4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KFifYr3fKyCsLz6VAnJYfV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.BufferedWriter;\n     4→import java.io.File;\n     5→import java.io.FileWriter;\n     6→import java.io.PrintWriter;\n     7→import java.io.Serializable;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import jakarta.batch.api.chunk.AbstractItemWriter;\n    10→import jakarta.batch.runtime.context.JobContext;\n    11→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    14→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    18→\n    19→@Dependent\n    20→@Named(\"EventItemWriter\")\n    21→public class EventItemWriter extends AbstractItemWriter {\n    22→\n    23→  private static final String ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY = \"archive_directory\";\n    24→\n    25→  @Inject\n    26→  private JobContext jobContext;\n    27→  @Inject\n    28→  private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    29→\n    30→  @Override\n    31→  public void open(Serializable checkpoint) throws Exception {\n    32→    File archiveDirectory = new File(jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY));\n    33→\n    34→    if (!archiveDirectory.exists()) {\n    35→      archiveDirectory.mkdirs();\n    36→    }\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  @Override\n    40→  @Transactional\n    41→  public void writeItems(List<Object> items) throws Exception {\n    42→    try (PrintWriter archive =\n    43→        new PrintWriter(\n    44→            new BufferedWriter(\n    45→                new FileWriter(\n    46→                    jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY)\n    47→                        + \"/archive_\"\n    48→                        + jobContext.getJobName()\n    49→                        + \"_\"\n    50→                        + jobContext.getInstanceId()\n    51→                        + \".csv\",\n    52→                    true)))) {\n    53→\n    54→      items\n    55→          .stream()\n    56→          .map(item -> (HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt) item)\n    57→          .forEach(\n    58→              attempt -> {\n    59→                applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    60→                archive.println(\n    61→                    DateConverter.toString(attempt.getRegistrationTime())\n    62→                        + \",\"\n    63→                        + DateConverter.toString(attempt.getCompletionTime())\n    64→                        + \",\"\n    65→                        + attempt.getTrackingId()\n    66→                        + \",\"\n    67→                        + attempt.getVoyageNumber()\n    68→                        + \",\"\n    69→                        + attempt.getUnLocode()\n    70→                        + \",\"\n    71→                        + attempt.getType());\n    72→              });\n    73→    }\n    74→  }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"4879a636-41c5-49d3-bcb6-abbe07115d40"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X9udxx3KR2oUjETYgT9185","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Date;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     5→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     6→import jakarta.batch.api.listener.JobListener;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    10→\n    11→@Dependent\n    12→@Named(\"FileProcessorJobListener\")\n    13→public class FileProcessorJobListener implements JobListener {\n    14→\n    15→  @Inject\n    16→  private Logger logger;\n    17→\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public void beforeJob() throws Exception {\n    20→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Handling event file processor batch job starting at {0}\", new Date());\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  @Override\n    24→  public void afterJob() throws Exception {\n    25→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Handling event file processor batch job completed at {0}\", new Date());\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"ba16b6a5-cca1-4925-851a-962a4295b49b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ECWXamTbM4G6tKKC96y5ju","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.File;\n     4→import java.io.RandomAccessFile;\n     5→import java.io.Serializable;\n     6→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     7→import java.time.format.DateTimeParseException;\n     8→import java.util.Arrays;\n     9→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    10→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    11→import jakarta.batch.api.chunk.AbstractItemReader;\n    12→import jakarta.batch.runtime.context.JobContext;\n    13→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    14→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    15→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    22→\n    23→@Dependent\n    24→@Named(\"EventItemReader\")\n    25→public class EventItemReader extends AbstractItemReader {\n    26→\n    27→  private static final String UPLOAD_DIRECTORY = \"upload_directory\";\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject\n    30→  private Logger logger;\n    31→\n    32→  @Inject\n    33→  private JobContext jobContext;\n    34→  private EventFilesCheckpoint checkpoint;\n    35→  private RandomAccessFile currentFile;\n    36→\n    37→  @Override\n    38→  public void open(Serializable checkpoint) throws Exception {\n    39→    File uploadDirectory = new File(jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(UPLOAD_DIRECTORY));\n    40→\n    41→    if (checkpoint == null) {\n    42→      this.checkpoint = new EventFilesCheckpoint();\n    43→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Scanning upload directory: {0}\", uploadDirectory);\n    44→\n    45→      if (!uploadDirectory.exists()) {\n    46→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Upload directory does not exist, creating it\");\n    47→        uploadDirectory.mkdirs();\n    48→      } else {\n    49→        this.checkpoint.setFiles(Arrays.asList(uploadDirectory.listFiles()));\n    50→      }\n    51→    } else {\n    52→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Starting from previous checkpoint\");\n    53→      this.checkpoint = (EventFilesCheckpoint) checkpoint;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    File file = this.checkpoint.currentFile();\n    57→\n    58→    if (file == null) {\n    59→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"No files to process\");\n    60→      currentFile = null;\n    61→    } else {\n    62→      currentFile = new RandomAccessFile(file, \"r\");\n    63→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing file: {0}\", file);\n    64→      currentFile.seek(this.checkpoint.getFilePointer());\n    65→    }\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @Override\n    69→  public Object readItem() throws Exception {\n    70→    if (currentFile != null) {\n    71→      String line = currentFile.readLine();\n    72→\n    73→      if (line != null) {\n    74→        this.checkpoint.setFilePointer(currentFile.getFilePointer());\n    75→        return parseLine(line);\n    76→      } else {\n    77→        logger.log(\n    78→            Level.INFO, \"Finished processing file, deleting: {0}\", this.checkpoint.currentFile());\n    79→        currentFile.close();\n    80→        this.checkpoint.currentFile().delete();\n    81→        File nextFile = this.checkpoint.nextFile();\n    82→\n    83→        if (nextFile == null) {\n    84→          logger.log(Level.INFO, \"No more files to process\");\n    85→          return null;\n    86→        } else {\n    87→          currentFile = new RandomAccessFile(nextFile, \"r\");\n    88→          logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing file: {0}\", nextFile);\n    89→          return readItem();\n    90→        }\n    91→      }\n    92→    } else {\n    93→      return null;\n    94→    }\n    95→  }\n    96→\n    97→  private Object parseLine(String line) throws EventLineParseException {\n    98→    String[] result = line.split(\",\");\n    99→\n   100→    if (result.length != 5) {\n   101→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Wrong number of data elements\", line);\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    LocalDateTime completionTime = null;\n   105→\n   106→    try {\n   107→      completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(result[0]);\n   108→    } catch (DateTimeParseException e) {\n   109→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse completion time\", e, line);\n   110→    }\n   111→\n   112→    TrackingId trackingId = null;\n   113→\n   114→    try {\n   115→      trackingId = new TrackingId(result[1]);\n   116→    } catch (NullPointerException e) {\n   117→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse tracking ID\", e, line);\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    VoyageNumber voyageNumber = null;\n   121→\n   122→    try {\n   123→      if (!result[2].isEmpty()) {\n   124→        voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(result[2]);\n   125→      }\n   126→    } catch (NullPointerException e) {\n   127→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse voyage number\", e, line);\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    UnLocode unLocode = null;\n   131→\n   132→    try {\n   133→      unLocode = new UnLocode(result[3]);\n   134→    } catch (IllegalArgumentException | NullPointerException e) {\n   135→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse UN location code\", e, line);\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    HandlingEvent.Type eventType = null;\n   139→\n   140→    try {\n   141→      eventType = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(result[4]);\n   142→    } catch (IllegalArgumentException | NullPointerException e) {\n   143→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse event type\", e, line);\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n   147→        new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n   148→            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, eventType, unLocode);\n   149→\n   150→    return attempt;\n   151→  }\n   152→\n   153→  @Override\n   154→  public Serializable checkpointInfo() throws Exception {\n   155→    return this.checkpoint;\n   156→  }\n   157→}\n   158→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"52723a3c-0597-4ab7-b271-8d1203d76dc6"}
