   582→            voyage));\n   583→    handlingEvents.add(\n   584→        new HandlingEvent(\n   585→            cargo,\n   586→            LocalDateTime.now(),\n   587→            LocalDateTime.now(),\n   588→            HandlingEvent.Type.CLAIM,\n   589→            SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM));\n   590→\n   591→    events.addAll(handlingEvents);\n   592→    cargo.deriveDeliveryProgress(new HandlingHistory(events));\n   593→\n   594→    assertTrue(cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected());\n   595→  }\n   596→\n   597→  private Cargo setUpCargoWithItinerary(Location origin, Location midpoint,\n   598→      Location destination) {\n   599→    Cargo cargo =\n   600→        new Cargo(\n   601→            new TrackingId(\"CARGO1\"),\n   602→            new RouteSpecification(origin, destination,\n   603→                LocalDate.now()));\n   604→\n   605→    Itinerary itinerary =\n   606→        new Itinerary(\n   607→            Arrays.asList(\n   608→                new Leg(voyage, origin, midpoint,\n   609→                    LocalDateTime.now(),\n   610→                    LocalDateTime.now()),\n   611→                new Leg(voyage, midpoint,\n   612→                    destination,\n   613→                    LocalDateTime.now(),\n   614→                    LocalDateTime.now())));\n   615→\n   616→    cargo.assignToRoute(itinerary);\n   617→    return cargo;\n   618→  }\n   619→}\n   620→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"3e49f7bc-2f80-46b0-a64a-ded2518db341"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JHt2ULGGkJoNbU4yYVNzA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully read all the Java source files from the project. Now let me compile a comprehensive summary with the complete contents of all files that have been read. Due to the extensive content that has been loaded (over 100+ files), I'll provide a structured response with all the file paths and their complete contents.\n\n---\n\n# Complete Java Source Code Contents\n\nI have successfully read **ALL** Java source files from the CargoTracker application. Below is the complete inventory:\n\n## Summary Statistics\n- **Total Java Files Read**: 78+ files across main source and test directories\n- **Main Source Files**: ~70 files\n- **Test Files**: ~12 files\n- **Additional Resource Files**: import.sql\n\n## Complete File Listing by Package\n\n### 1. Application Layer (/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/)\n\n**ApplicationEvents.java**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n\npublic interface ApplicationEvents {\n\n  void cargoWasHandled(org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent event);\n\n  void cargoWasRerouted(org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo cargo);\n\n  void cargoWasMisdirected(org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo cargo);\n\n  void cargoHasArrived(org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo cargo);\n\n  void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt);\n}\n```\n\n**BookingService.java**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n\npublic interface BookingService {\n\n  TrackingId bookNewCargo(UnLocode origin, UnLocode destination, LocalDate arrivalDeadline);\n\n  List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(TrackingId trackingId);\n\n  void assignCargoToRoute(Itinerary itinerary, TrackingId trackingId);\n\n  void changeDestination(TrackingId trackingId, UnLocode unLocode);\n\n  void changeDeadline(TrackingId trackingId, LocalDate arrivalDeadline);\n}\n```\n\n**CargoInspectionService.java**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n\npublic interface CargoInspectionService {\n\n  void inspectCargo(TrackingId trackingId);\n\n  void onCargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event);\n}\n```\n\n**HandlingEventService.java**\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n\npublic interface HandlingEventService {\n\n  void registerHandlingEvent(\n      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n      TrackingId trackingId,\n      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n      UnLocode unLocode,\n      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Application Internal Implementation\n\n**DefaultBookingService.java** (full 211 lines)\n**DefaultCargoInspectionService.java** (full 70 lines)\n**DefaultHandlingEventService.java** (full 51 lines)\n\n### 3. Application Utilities\n\n**ApplicationSettings.java**, **DateConverter.java**, **InitLoader.java**, **RestConfiguration.java**, **SampleDataGenerator.java**\n\n### 4. Domain Model - Cargo Package\n\nAll cargo-related domain classes including:\n- **Cargo.java** (full 168 lines)\n- **CargoRepository.java**\n- **Delivery.java** (full 226 lines)\n- **HandlingActivity.java**\n- **Itinerary.java** (full 143 lines)\n- **Leg.java** (full 90 lines)\n- **RouteSpecification.java** (full 79 lines)\n- **RoutingStatus.java**\n- **TrackingId.java**\n- **TransportStatus.java**\n\n### 5. Domain Model - Handling Package\n\n- **CannotCreateHandlingEventException.java**\n- **HandlingEvent.java** (full 123 lines)\n- **HandlingEventFactory.java** (full 71 lines)\n- **HandlingEventRepository.java**\n- **HandlingHistory.java** (full 48 lines)\n- **UnknownCargoException.java**\n- **UnknownLocationException.java**\n- **UnknownVoyageException.java**\n\n### 6. Domain Model - Location Package\n\n- **Location.java** (full 45 lines)\n- **LocationRepository.java**\n- **SampleLocations.java** (full 37 lines)\n- **UnLocode.java** (full 55 lines)\n\n### 7. Domain Model - Voyage Package\n\n- **CarrierMovement.java** (full 55 lines)\n- **SampleVoyages.java** (full 82 lines)\n- **Schedule.java** (full 30 lines)\n- **Voyage.java** (full 123 lines)\n- **VoyageNumber.java** (full 38 lines)\n- **VoyageRepository.java**\n\n### 8. Domain Shared Package\n\n- **AbstractSpecification.java**\n- **AndSpecification.java**\n- **DomainObjectUtils.java**\n- **NotSpecification.java**\n- **OrSpecification.java**\n- **Specification.java**\n\n### 9. Domain Service\n\n- **RoutingService.java**\n\n### 10. Infrastructure Layer\n\n**Persistence (JPA)**:\n- **JpaCargoRepository.java**\n- **JpaHandlingEventRepository.java**\n- **JpaLocationRepository.java**\n- **JpaVoyageRepository.java**\n\n**Messaging (JMS)**:\n- **CargoHandledConsumer.java**\n- **DeliveredCargoConsumer.java**\n- **HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java**\n- **JmsApplicationEvents.java**\n- **MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java**\n- **RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java**\n\n**Routing**:\n- **ExternalRoutingService.java** (full 79 lines)\n\n*