a**\n- **HandlingEventServiceTest.java**\n- **TestDataGenerator.java**\n\n**Domain Tests**:\n- **CargoTest.java** (full 620 lines - extensive domain tests)\n- **HandlingEventTest.java** (full 139 lines)\n- **HandlingHistoryTest.java** (full 81 lines)\n- **ItineraryTest.java** (full 194 lines)\n- **RouteSpecificationTest.java** (full 102 lines)\n\n**Infrastructure Tests**:\n- **ExternalRoutingServiceTest.java**\n\n**Scenario Tests**:\n- **CargoLifecycleScenarioTest.java** (full 425 lines - comprehensive lifecycle test)\n\n### 16. Resources\n\n**/src/main/resources/import.sql**\n```sql\n-- Sample locations\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (1, 'CNHKG', 'Hongkong');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (2, 'AUMEL', 'Melbourne');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (3, 'SESTO', 'Stockholm');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (4, 'FIHEL', 'Helsinki');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (5, 'USCHI', 'Chicago');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (6, 'JNTKO', 'Tokyo');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (7, 'DEHAM', 'Hamburg');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (8, 'CNSHA', 'Shanghai');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (9, 'NLRTM', 'Rotterdam');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (10, 'SEGOT', 'Gothenburg');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (11, 'CNHGH', 'Hangzhou');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (12, 'USNYC', 'New York');\nINSERT INTO Location (id, unlocode, name) VALUES (13, 'USDAL', 'Dallas');\n```\n\n## Key Architecture Observations\n\nThe application follows **Domain-Driven Design (DDD)** principles with clear separation of:\n\n1. **Application Layer**: Services orchestrating business operations\n2. **Domain Layer**: Core business logic, entities, value objects, and domain services\n3. **Infrastructure Layer**: JPA repositories, JMS messaging, external service integrations\n4. **Interfaces Layer**: Web controllers, REST APIs, DTOs, and facades\n\nThe codebase demonstrates:\n- Clean architecture with dependency inversion\n- Rich domain model with behavior encapsulated in entities\n- Event-driven architecture using JMS\n- Separation of concerns with DTOs and assemblers\n- Comprehensive unit and integration tests\n- Support for batch processing (file-based event handling)\n- Real-time updates via Server-Sent Events (SSE)\n- Integration with external routing services\n\nAll files have been successfully read and their complete contents are available in the response above."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"d2226bf0-2b39-4a15-b236-ba7dbf060f36"}
