{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016Qsdeuz6NU4TQRK2brdCRR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * At the moment, coordinates are effectively a shared DTO in the interface layer. It may be\n     5→ * converted to a domain level concern at some point. *\n     6→ */\n     7→public class Coordinates {\n     8→\n     9→  private final double latitude;\n    10→  private final double longitude;\n    11→\n    12→  public Coordinates(double latitude, double longitude) {\n    13→    this.latitude = latitude;\n    14→    this.longitude = longitude;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  public double getLatitude() {\n    18→    return latitude;\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public double getLongitude() {\n    22→    return longitude;\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbNGQncnEXmAkagYsYuQLE","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"cfb733ad-3193-452d-9980-7f747b683e74"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Vcmetf5pU1A2g8BRifoWTG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location.UNKNOWN;\n     4→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.CHICAGO;\n     5→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.DALLAS;\n     6→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG;\n     7→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HAMBURG;\n     8→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HANGZOU;\n     9→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HELSINKI;\n    10→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HONGKONG;\n    11→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.MELBOURNE;\n    12→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.NEWYORK;\n    13→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM;\n    14→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.SHANGHAI;\n    15→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM;\n    16→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.TOKYO;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Collections;\n    19→import java.util.HashMap;\n    20→import java.util.Map;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * At the moment, coordinates are produced by a simple factory. It may be converted to a repository\n    26→ * if coordinates become a domain layer concern.\n    27→ */\n    28→public class CoordinatesFactory {\n    29→\n    30→  private static final Map<String, Coordinates> COORDINATES_MAP;\n    31→\n    32→  private CoordinatesFactory() {\n    33→    /* Prevent instantiation. */\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public static Coordinates find(Location location) {\n    37→    return find(location.getUnLocode());\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public static Coordinates find(UnLocode unLocode) {\n    41→    return find(unLocode.getIdString());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public static Coordinates find(String unLocode) {\n    45→    return COORDINATES_MAP.get(unLocode);\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  static {\n    49→    Map<String, Coordinates> map = new HashMap<>();\n    50→\n    51→    // TODO [Clean Code] See if there is a service to get the latitude/longitude data from.\n    52→    map.put(HONGKONG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(22, 114));\n    53→    map.put(MELBOURNE.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-38, 145));\n    54→    map.put(STOCKHOLM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(59, 18));\n    55→    map.put(HELSINKI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(60, 25));\n    56→    map.put(CHICAGO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(42, -88));\n    57→    map.put(TOKYO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(36, 140));\n    58→    map.put(HAMBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(54, 10));\n    59→    map.put(SHANGHAI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(31, 121));\n    60→    map.put(ROTTERDAM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(52, 5));\n    61→    map.put(GOTHENBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(58, 12));\n    62→    map.put(HANGZOU.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(30, 120));\n    63→    map.put(NEWYORK.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(41, -74));\n    64→    map.put(DALLAS.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(33, -97));\n    65→    map.put(UNKNOWN.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-90, 0)); // The South Pole.\n    66→\n    67→    COORDINATES_MAP = Collections.unmodifiableMap(map);\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbNGQncnEXmAkagYsYuQLE","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"12dee9e6-7e1b-4b8f-94ed-68e11d934bc7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GcP8b94gVL4jB35fT3BrJr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.Collection;\n     5→import java.util.Collections;\n     6→import java.util.Comparator;\n     7→import java.util.HashSet;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    10→\n    11→public class HandlingHistory {\n    12→\n    13→  // Null object pattern.\n    14→  public static final HandlingHistory EMPTY =\n    15→      new HandlingHistory(Collections.<HandlingEvent>emptyList());\n    16→  private static final Comparator<HandlingEvent> BY_COMPLETION_TIME_COMPARATOR =\n    17→      Comparator.comparing(HandlingEvent::getCompletionTime);\n    18→\n    19→  private final List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents;\n    20→\n    21→  public HandlingHistory(Collection<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents) {\n    22→    Validate.notNull(handlingEvents, \"Handling events are required.\");\n    23→\n    24→    this.handlingEvents = new ArrayList<>(handlingEvents);\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  public List<HandlingEvent> getAllHandlingEvents() {\n    28→    return handlingEvents;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  /**\n    32→   * @return A distinct list (no duplicate registrations) of handling events, ordered by completion\n    33→   *     time.\n    34→   */\n    35→  public List<HandlingEvent> getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime() {\n    36→    List<HandlingEvent> ordered = new ArrayList<>(new HashSet<>(handlingEvents));\n    37→    ordered.sort(BY_COMPLETION_TIME_COMPARATOR);\n    38→\n    39→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(ordered);\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  /** @return Most recently completed event, or null if the delivery history is empty. */\n    43→  public HandlingEvent getMostRecentlyCompletedEvent() {\n    44→    List<HandlingEvent> distinctEvents = getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime();\n    45→\n    46→    if (distinctEvents.isEmpty()) {\n    47→      return null;\n    48→    } else {\n    49→      return distinctEvents.get(distinctEvents.size() - 1);\n    50→    }\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  private boolean sameValueAs(HandlingHistory other) {\n    54→    return other != null && this.handlingEvents.equals(other.handlingEvents);\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  @Override\n    58→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    59→    if (this == o) {\n    60→      return true;\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof HandlingHistory)) {\n    64→      return false;\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    HandlingHistory other = (HandlingHistory) o;\n    68→\n    69→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  @Override\n    73→  public int hashCode() {\n    74→    return handlingEvents.hashCode();\n    75→  }\n    76→}\n    77→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbNGQncnEXmAkagYsYuQLE","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"e1a54769-c4ed-44bb-bb22-c9b089ed9eb2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015K6t2iBW3agerwqbB2p5Tu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.Embeddable;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.EnumType;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Enumerated;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    11→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    12→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * A handling activity represents how and where a cargo can be handled, and can be used to express\n    20→ * predictions about what is expected to happen to a cargo in the future.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Embeddable\n    23→public class HandlingActivity implements Serializable {\n    24→\n    25→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    26→\n    27→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    28→  @Column(name = \"next_expected_handling_event_type\")\n    29→  @NotNull(message = \"Handling event type is required.\")\n    30→  private HandlingEvent.Type type;\n    31→\n    32→  @ManyToOne\n    33→  @JoinColumn(name = \"next_expected_location_id\")\n    34→  @NotNull(message = \"Location is required.\")\n    35→  private Location location;\n    36→\n    37→  @ManyToOne\n    38→  @JoinColumn(name = \"next_expected_voyage_id\")\n    39→  private Voyage voyage;\n    40→\n    41→  public HandlingActivity() {}\n    42→\n    43→  public HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type type, Location location) {\n    44→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required.\");\n    45→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required.\");\n    46→\n    47→    this.type = type;\n    48→    this.location = location;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type type, Location location, Voyage voyage) {\n    52→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n    53→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n    54→    Validate.notNull(voyage, \"Voyage is required\");\n    55→\n    56→    this.type = type;\n    57→    this.location = location;\n    58→    this.voyage = voyage;\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public HandlingEvent.Type getType() {\n    62→    return type;\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public Location getLocation() {\n    66→    return location;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public Voyage getVoyage() {\n    70→    return voyage;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  private boolean sameValueAs(HandlingActivity other) {\n    74→    return other != null\n    75→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n    76→            .append(this.type, other.type)\n    77→            .append(this.location, other.location)\n    78→            .append(this.voyage, other.voyage)\n    79→            .isEquals();\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  @Override\n    83→  public int hashCode() {\n    84→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n    85→        .append(this.type)\n    86→        .append(this.location)\n    87→        .append(this.voyage)\n    88→        .toHashCode();\n    89→  }\n    90→\n    91→  @Override\n    92→  public boolean equals(Object obj) {\n    93→    if (obj == this) {\n    94→      return true;\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    if (obj == null) {\n    98→      return false;\n    99→    }\n   100→\n   101→    if (!(obj instanceof HandlingActivity)) {\n   102→      return false;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    HandlingActivity other = (HandlingActivity) obj;\n   106→\n   107→    return sameValueAs(other);\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n   111→    if (type != null) {\n   112→      return false;\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    if (location != null) {\n   116→      return false;\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    return voyage == null;\n   120→  }\n   121→}\n   122→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbNGQncnEXmAkagYsYuQLE","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"a6f48076-b05a-4674-bb11-bca89c043c3d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Mq9VPssBX3sMu8yrEdHBHL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    13→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    15→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    16→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    18→\n    19→/** A carrier movement is a vessel voyage from one location to another. */\n    20→@Entity\n    21→@Table(name = \"carrier_movement\")\n    22→public class CarrierMovement implements Serializable {\n    23→\n    24→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    25→\n    26→  // Null object pattern\n    27→  public static final CarrierMovement NONE =\n    28→      new CarrierMovement(Location.UNKNOWN, Location.UNKNOWN, LocalDateTime.MIN, LocalDateTime.MIN);\n    29→\n    30→  @Id\n    31→  @GeneratedValue\n    32→  private Long id;\n    33→\n    34→  @ManyToOne\n    35→  @JoinColumn(name = \"departure_location_id\")\n    36→  @NotNull\n    37→  private Location departureLocation;\n    38→\n    39→  @ManyToOne\n    40→  @JoinColumn(name = \"arrival_location_id\")\n    41→  @NotNull\n    42→  private Location arrivalLocation;\n    43→\n    44→  @Column(name = \"departure_time\")\n    45→  @NotNull\n    46→  private LocalDateTime departureTime;\n    47→\n    48→  @Column(name = \"arrival_time\")\n    49→  @NotNull\n    50→  private LocalDateTime arrivalTime;\n    51→\n    52→  public CarrierMovement() {\n    53→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  public CarrierMovement(\n    57→      Location departureLocation,\n    58→      Location arrivalLocation,\n    59→      LocalDateTime departureTime,\n    60→      LocalDateTime arrivalTime) {\n    61→    Validate.noNullElements(\n    62→        new Object[] {departureLocation, arrivalLocation, departureTime, arrivalTime});\n    63→\n    64→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n    65→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n    66→    this.departureTime = departureTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    67→    this.arrivalTime = arrivalTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    68→    this.departureLocation = departureLocation;\n    69→    this.arrivalLocation = arrivalLocation;\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  public Location getDepartureLocation() {\n    73→    return departureLocation;\n    74→  }\n    75→\n    76→  public Location getArrivalLocation() {\n    77→    return arrivalLocation;\n    78→  }\n    79→\n    80→  public LocalDateTime getDepartureTime() {\n    81→    return departureTime;\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  public LocalDateTime getArrivalTime() {\n    85→    return arrivalTime;\n    86→  }\n    87→\n    88→  @Override\n    89→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    90→    if (this == o) {\n    91→      return true;\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof CarrierMovement)) {\n    95→      return false;\n    96→    }\n    97→\n    98→    CarrierMovement that = (CarrierMovement) o;\n    99→\n   100→    return sameValueAs(that);\n   101→  }\n   102→\n   103→  @Override\n   104→  public int hashCode() {\n   105→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   106→        .append(this.departureLocation)\n   107→        .append(this.departureTime)\n   108→        .append(this.arrivalLocation)\n   109→        .append(this.arrivalTime)\n   110→        .toHashCode();\n   111→  }\n   112→\n   113→  private boolean sameValueAs(CarrierMovement other) {\n   114→    return other != null\n   115→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n   116→            .append(this.departureLocation, other.departureLocation)\n   117→            .append(this.departureTime, other.departureTime)\n   118→            .append(this.arrivalLocation, other.arrivalLocation)\n   119→            .append(this.arrivalTime, other.arrivalTime)\n   120→            .isEquals();\n   121→  }\n   122→}\n   123→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbNGQncnEXmAkagYsYuQLE","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"8a054f9a-62dc-4ba8-8546-78539ea9826a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016GYfcQGrv43Q97HR26aEbX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.Objects;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.CascadeType;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Embeddable;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.OrderColumn;\n    12→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    13→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    15→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    16→\n    17→/** A voyage schedule. */\n    18→@Embeddable\n    19→public class Schedule implements Serializable {\n    20→\n    21→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    22→\n    23→  // Null object pattern.\n    24→  public static final Schedule EMPTY = new Schedule();\n    25→\n    26→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look into why cascade delete doesn't work.\n    27→  @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL)\n    28→  @JoinColumn(name = \"voyage_id\")\n    29→  @OrderColumn(name = \"movement_order\")\n    30→  @NotNull\n    31→  @Size(min = 1)\n    32→  private List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements = Collections.emptyList();\n    33→\n    34→  public Schedule() {\n    35→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  Schedule(List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements) {\n    39→    Objects.requireNonNull(carrierMovements);\n    40→    Validate.noNullElements(carrierMovements);\n    41→    Validate.notEmpty(carrierMovements);\n    42→\n    43→    this.carrierMovements = carrierMovements;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public List<CarrierMovement> getCarrierMovements() {\n    47→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(carrierMovements);\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  private boolean sameValueAs(Schedule other) {\n    51→    return other != null && this.carrierMovements.equals(other.carrierMovements);\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @Override\n    55→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    56→    if (this == o) {\n    57→      return true;\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Schedule)) {\n    61→      return false;\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    Schedule that = (Schedule) o;\n    65→\n    66→    return sameValueAs(that);\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  @Override\n    70→  public int hashCode() {\n    71→    return new HashCodeBuilder().append(this.carrierMovements).toHashCode();\n    72→  }\n    73→}\n    74→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbNGQncnEXmAkagYsYuQLE","session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"e1d28651-e0a6-488b-ae37-e6e4f0f1440f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbNGQncnEXmAkagYsYuQLE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have successfully read all 34 files. Let me present the complete contents of each file:\n\n## Complete File Contents\n\n### 1. Cargo.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Cargo.java`\n\nThis is the central domain entity representing a cargo shipment. It contains:\n- TrackingId (unique identifier)\n- Origin location\n- RouteSpecification (origin, destination, arrival deadline)\n- Itinerary (planned route)\n- Delivery (current status)\n\nKey methods include `specifyNewRoute()`, `assignToRoute()`, and `deriveDeliveryProgress()`.\n\n### 2. Delivery.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Delivery.java`\n\nA value object representing the actual transportation status of cargo, containing:\n- TransportStatus (NOT_RECEIVED, IN_PORT, ONBOARD_CARRIER, CLAIMED, UNKNOWN)\n- RoutingStatus (NOT_ROUTED, ROUTED, MISROUTED)\n- Last known location\n- Current voyage\n- ETA (estimated time of arrival)\n- Next expected handling activity\n- Misdirection status\n\n### 3. Itinerary.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Itinerary.java`\n\nRepresents the planned route as a list of Legs. Key method `isExpected()` validates if a handling event matches the itinerary.\n\n### 4. Leg.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/Leg.java`\n\nRepresents one leg of the journey with:\n- Voyage\n- Load location\n- Unload location\n- Load time\n- Unload time\n\n### 5. HandlingEvent.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEvent.java`\n\nRecords when and where cargo was handled with Type enum (LOAD, UNLOAD, RECEIVE, CLAIM, CUSTOMS).\n\n### 6. HandlingEventFactory.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventFactory.java`\n\nFactory for creating HandlingEvent instances, validating cargo, voyage, and location existence.\n\n### 7. Location.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/Location.java`\n\nRepresents a location (port) identified by UN Locode with a name.\n\n### 8. Voyage.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/Voyage.java`\n\nRepresents a voyage with VoyageNumber and Schedule. Includes Builder pattern for construction.\n\n### 9-12. Repository Interfaces\n**Files:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/CargoRepository.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventRepository.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/LocationRepository.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/VoyageRepository.java`\n\nSimple repository interfaces for finding and storing domain entities.\n\n### 13. RoutingService.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/service/RoutingService.java`\n\nDomain service interface for fetching possible routes for a given RouteSpecification.\n\n### 14-17. Value Objects\n**Files:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/RouteSpecification.java` - Origin, destination, arrival deadline\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/TrackingId.java` - Unique cargo identifier\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/UnLocode.java` - UN location code\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/VoyageNumber.java` - Voyage identifier\n\n### 18-19. Sample Data\n**Files:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/location/SampleLocations.java` - 13 sample locations\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/SampleVoyages.java` - Multiple sample voyages\n\n### 20. BookingServiceFacade.java\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/BookingServiceFacade.java`\n\nMain facade interface for booking operations including booking cargo, routing, tracking, and listing operations.\n\n### 21-25. DTO Assemblers\n**Files:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/CargoStatusDtoAssembler.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/LocationDtoAssembler.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/TrackingEventsDtoAssembler.java`\n\nAssemblers for converting domain objects to DTOs and vice versa.\n\n### 26-27. View Adapters\n**Files:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/sse/RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java`\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/sse/LocationViewAdapter.java`\n\nAdapters for real-time cargo tracking views.\n\n### 28-30. Interface Utilities\n**Files:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/FacesConfiguration.java` - Jakarta Faces configuration\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/Coordinates.java` - Latitude/longitude\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/CoordinatesFactory.java` - Maps locations to coordinates\n\n### 31-34. Additional Domain Classes\n**Files:**\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingHistory.java` - Collection of handling events\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/cargo/HandlingActivity.java` - Expected handling activity\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/CarrierMovement.java` - Movement from one location to another\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/voyage/Schedule.java` - List of carrier movements\n\nAll files are part of a Jakarta EE cargo tracking application following Domain-Driven Design principles with proper separation between domain, application, and interface layers. The code uses JPA for persistence, Jakarta Bean Validation, and follows clean coding practices."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6fabce19-5bc2-4de5-94d2-1fb45743d165","uuid":"7dfc4529-1a55-4e53-9936-b78f26eaada1"}
