{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MDBwWBsYe2QJ6oGSSwn8b1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     3→    xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     4→    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     5→\n     6→    <parent>\n     7→        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n     8→        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>\n     9→        <version>3.2.5</version>\n    10→        <relativePath/>\n    11→    </parent>\n    12→\n    13→    <groupId>org.eclipse.ee4j</groupId>\n    14→    <artifactId>cargo-tracker</artifactId>\n    15→    <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n    16→    <packaging>jar</packaging>\n    17→    <name>cargo-tracker</name>\n    18→    <description>Cargo Tracker - Spring Boot</description>\n    19→\n    20→    <properties>\n    21→        <java.version>21</java.version>\n    22→        <maven.compiler.release>21</maven.compiler.release>\n    23→        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    24→    </properties>\n    25→\n    26→    <dependencies>\n    27→        <!-- Spring Boot Starters -->\n    28→        <dependency>\n    29→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    30→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>\n    31→        </dependency>\n    32→        <dependency>\n    33→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    34→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>\n    35→        </dependency>\n    36→        <dependency>\n    37→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    38→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-validation</artifactId>\n    39→        </dependency>\n    40→        <dependency>\n    41→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    42→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-actuator</artifactId>\n    43→        </dependency>\n    44→        <dependency>\n    45→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    46→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-artemis</artifactId>\n    47→        </dependency>\n    48→\n    49→        <!-- H2 Database -->\n    50→        <dependency>\n    51→            <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    52→            <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    53→            <scope>runtime</scope>\n    54→        </dependency>\n    55→\n    56→        <!-- Jackson for JSON/XML -->\n    57→        <dependency>\n    58→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype</groupId>\n    59→            <artifactId>jackson-datatype-jsr310</artifactId>\n    60→        </dependency>\n    61→\n    62→        <!-- Test -->\n    63→        <dependency>\n    64→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    65→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-test</artifactId>\n    66→            <scope>test</scope>\n    67→        </dependency>\n    68→    </dependencies>\n    69→\n    70→    <build>\n    71→        <plugins>\n    72→            <plugin>\n    73→                <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    74→                <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    75→            </plugin>\n    76→            <plugin>\n    77→                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n    78→                <configuration>\n    79→                    <release>21</release>\n    80→                    <parameters>true</parameters>\n    81→                </configuration>\n    82→            </plugin>\n    83→        </plugins>\n    84→    </build>\n    85→</project>\n    86→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or